20namespace zlib_internal {
21
22// The difference in bytes between a zlib header and a gzip header.
23const size_t kGzipZlibHeaderDifferenceBytes = 16;
24
25// Pass an integer greater than the following get a gzip header instead of a
26// zlib header when calling deflateInit2() and inflateInit2().
27const int kWindowBitsToGetGzipHeader = 16;
28
29// This describes the amount of memory zlib uses to compress data. It can go
30// from 1 to 9, with 8 being the default. For details, see:
31// http://www.zlib.net/manual.html (search for memLevel).
32const int kZlibMemoryLevel = 8;
33
34// The expected compressed size is based on the input size factored by
35// internal Zlib constants (e.g. window size, etc) plus the wrapper
36// header size.
37uLongf GzipExpectedCompressedSize(uLongf input_size) {
38 return kGzipZlibHeaderDifferenceBytes + compressBound(input_size);
39}
40
41// The expected decompressed size is stored in the last
42// 4 bytes of |input| in LE. See https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1952#page-5
43uint32_t GetGzipUncompressedSize(const Bytef* compressed_data, size_t length) {
44 uint32_t size;
45 if (length < sizeof(size))
46 return 0;
47
48 memcpy(&size, &compressed_data[length - sizeof(size)], sizeof(size));
49#if __BYTE_ORDER__ == __ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN__
50 return size;
51#else
52 return __builtin_bswap32(size);
53#endif
54}
55
56// The number of window bits determines the type of wrapper to use - see
57// https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/zlib/zlib.h?l=566
58inline int ZlibStreamWrapperType(WrapperType type) {
59 if (type == ZLIB) // zlib DEFLATE stream wrapper
60 return MAX_WBITS;
61 if (type == GZIP) // gzip DEFLATE stream wrapper
62 return MAX_WBITS + kWindowBitsToGetGzipHeader;
63 if (type == ZRAW) // no wrapper, use raw DEFLATE
64 return -MAX_WBITS;
65 return 0;
66}

68int GzipCompressHelper(Bytef* dest,
69 uLongf* dest_length,
70 const Bytef* source,
71 uLong source_length,
72 void* (*malloc_fn)(size_t),
73 void (*free_fn)(void*)) {
74 return CompressHelper(GZIP, dest, dest_length, source, source_length,
75 Z_DEFAULT_COMPRESSION, malloc_fn, free_fn);
76}
77
78// This code is taken almost verbatim from third_party/zlib/compress.c. The only
79// difference is deflateInit2() is called which allows different window bits to
80// be set. > 16 causes a gzip header to be emitted rather than a zlib header,
81// and negative causes no header to emitted.
82//
83// Compression level can be a number from 1-9, with 1 being the fastest, 9 being
84// the best compression. The default, which the GZIP helper uses, is 6.
85int CompressHelper(WrapperType wrapper_type,
86 Bytef* dest,
87 uLongf* dest_length,
88 const Bytef* source,
89 uLong source_length,
90 int compression_level,
91 void* (*malloc_fn)(size_t),
92 void (*free_fn)(void*)) {
93 if (compression_level < 0 || compression_level > 9) {
94 compression_level = Z_DEFAULT_COMPRESSION;
95 }
96
97 z_stream stream;
98
99 // FIXME(cavalcantii): z_const is not defined as 'const'.
100 stream.next_in = static_cast<z_const Bytef*>(const_cast<Bytef*>(source));
101 stream.avail_in = static_cast<uInt>(source_length);
102 stream.next_out = dest;
103 stream.avail_out = static_cast<uInt>(*dest_length);
104 if (static_cast<uLong>(stream.avail_out) != *dest_length)
105 return Z_BUF_ERROR;
106
107 // Cannot convert capturing lambdas to function pointers directly, hence the
108 // structure.
109 struct MallocFreeFunctions {
110 void* (*malloc_fn)(size_t);
111 void (*free_fn)(void*);
112 } malloc_free = {malloc_fn, free_fn};
113
114 if (malloc_fn) {
115 if (!free_fn)
116 return Z_BUF_ERROR;
117
118 auto zalloc = [](void* opaque, uInt items, uInt size) {
119 return reinterpret_cast<MallocFreeFunctions*>(opaque)->malloc_fn(items *
120 size);
121 };
122 auto zfree = [](void* opaque, void* address) {
123 return reinterpret_cast<MallocFreeFunctions*>(opaque)->free_fn(address);
124 };
125
126 stream.zalloc = static_cast<alloc_func>(zalloc);
127 stream.zfree = static_cast<free_func>(zfree);
128 stream.opaque = static_cast<voidpf>(&malloc_free);
129 } else {
130 stream.zalloc = static_cast<alloc_func>(0);
131 stream.zfree = static_cast<free_func>(0);
132 stream.opaque = static_cast<voidpf>(0);
133 }
134
135 int err = deflateInit2(&stream, compression_level, Z_DEFLATED,
136 ZlibStreamWrapperType(wrapper_type), kZlibMemoryLevel,
137 Z_DEFAULT_STRATEGY);
138 if (err != Z_OK)
139 return err;
140
141 // This has to exist outside of the if statement to prevent it going off the
142 // stack before deflate(), which will use this object.
143 gz_header gzip_header;
144 if (wrapper_type == GZIP) {
145 memset(&gzip_header, 0, sizeof(gzip_header));
146 err = deflateSetHeader(&stream, &gzip_header);
147 if (err != Z_OK)
148 return err;
149 }
150
151 err = deflate(&stream, Z_FINISH);
152 if (err != Z_STREAM_END) {
153 deflateEnd(&stream);
154 return err == Z_OK ? Z_BUF_ERROR : err;
155 }
156 *dest_length = stream.total_out;
157
158 err = deflateEnd(&stream);
159 return err;
160}
161
162int GzipUncompressHelper(Bytef* dest,
163 uLongf* dest_length,
164 const Bytef* source,
165 uLong source_length) {
166 return UncompressHelper(GZIP, dest, dest_length, source, source_length);
167}
168
169// This code is taken almost verbatim from third_party/zlib/uncompr.c. The only
170// difference is inflateInit2() is called which allows different window bits to
171// be set. > 16 causes a gzip header to be emitted rather than a zlib header,
172// and negative causes no header to emitted.
173int UncompressHelper(WrapperType wrapper_type,
174 Bytef* dest,
175 uLongf* dest_length,
176 const Bytef* source,
177 uLong source_length) {
178 z_stream stream;
179
180 // FIXME(cavalcantii): z_const is not defined as 'const'.
181 stream.next_in = static_cast<z_const Bytef*>(const_cast<Bytef*>(source));
182 stream.avail_in = static_cast<uInt>(source_length);
183 if (static_cast<uLong>(stream.avail_in) != source_length)
184 return Z_BUF_ERROR;
185
186 stream.next_out = dest;
187 stream.avail_out = static_cast<uInt>(*dest_length);
188 if (static_cast<uLong>(stream.avail_out) != *dest_length)
189 return Z_BUF_ERROR;
190
191 stream.zalloc = static_cast<alloc_func>(0);
192 stream.zfree = static_cast<free_func>(0);
193
194 int err = inflateInit2(&stream, ZlibStreamWrapperType(wrapper_type));
195 if (err != Z_OK)
196 return err;
197
198 err = inflate(&stream, Z_FINISH);
199 if (err != Z_STREAM_END) {
200 inflateEnd(&stream);
201 if (err == Z_NEED_DICT || (err == Z_BUF_ERROR && stream.avail_in == 0))
202 return Z_DATA_ERROR;
203 return err;
204 }
205 *dest_length = stream.total_out;
206
207 err = inflateEnd(&stream);
208 return err;
209}
